[normal]Network Rail i
[normal]s planning to build additional platforms at Leeds to increase station capacity. The cost of one platform can be avoided by creating a through service from Harrogate via Horsforth returning to Harrogate via Wetherby as in a teardrop and vice versa. This wou
[normal]ld double the service from Harrogate by still using four car units and serve reopened stations on the Wetherby route. Platform blocking would be abolished as through platforms would be used with much reduced dwell time.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Leeds Metro has been planning a shu
[normal]ttle service from Micklefield to Leeds as a park and ride service. Again there is the problem of turnround time at Micklefield on a very busy route and junction even if a dedicated turnround siding and platform are provided. How much better it would be to 
[normal]continue beyond Micklefield to Church Fenton a few miles further on and return to Leeds via Tadcaster, Wetherby and Cross Gates and vice versa in another teardrop on the proposed reinstated line.
[normal] 
[normal]This would improve interchange at Church Fenton if the adjac
[normal]ent former RAF Church Fenton is converted into a Yorkshire airport. The other Yorkshire airports at Leeds/Bradford and Doncaster are not rail connected. At Leeds through platforms can be used with the same train continuing to say Bradford, Skipton, Ilkley,
[normal] Huddersfield or Hebden Bridge via Halifax. This will reduce platform blocking again at Leeds west end freeing up 
[normal]another bay platform. The sketch map accompanying this submission will aid explanation of concept.
